<main class="container mx-auto p-8 text-center">

    <!-- About Toronto Section -->
    <section class="about-toronto">
        <h1 class="main__title">About Toronto</h1>
        <p class="main__text">Toronto is Canada's largest city and a global hub for business, arts, and culture. 
            With over 2.9 million residents, it is one of the most diverse cities in the world.</p>
        <p class="main__text">Whether you're interested in history, food, entertainment, or outdoor activities, 
            Toronto has something for everyone.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Places to Visit in Canada -->
    <section class="places-to-visit">
        <h2 class="main__title">Top Places to Visit in Canada</h2>
        <div class="places-grid">
            <div class="place-card">
                <h3 class="place-card__title">Niagara Falls</h3>
                <p class="place-card__description">One of the most iconic natural wonders in the world, Niagara Falls offers breathtaking views and thrilling boat tours.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="place-card">
                <h3 class="place-card__title">Banff National Park</h3>
                <p class="place-card__description">Located in the heart of the Canadian Rockies, Banff National Park is a paradise for outdoor enthusiasts, offering hiking, skiing, and stunning mountain views.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="place-card">
                <h3 class="place-card__title">Old Quebec City</h3>
                <p class="place-card__description">With its cobblestone streets and European-style architecture, Old Quebec offers a charming and historical experience for visitors.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Must-Try Foods in Canada -->
    <section class="must-try-foods">
        <h2 class="main__title">Must-Try Canadian Foods</h2>
        <p class="main__text">Canada has a diverse culinary scene, with flavors influenced by its multicultural population. Don't miss out on these iconic Canadian dishes:</p>
        <ul class="food-list">
            <li><strong>Poutine</strong>: A Quebecois classic made of crispy fries topped with cheese curds and smothered in gravy.</li>
            <li><strong>Butter Tarts</strong>: A sweet pastry filled with caramelized sugar and butter, a true Canadian dessert.</li>
            <li><strong>Caesars</strong>: A Canadian cocktail made with vodka, Clamato juice, hot sauce, and Worcestershire sauce, often served with a celery stick.</li>
            <li><strong>Tourtière</strong>: A traditional meat pie often served during the holidays, made with pork, beef, and spices.</li>
            <li><strong>Maple Syrup</strong>: Canada is famous for its high-quality maple syrup, perfect for drizzling on pancakes, waffles, and French toast.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Outdoor Activities to Enjoy -->
    <section class="outdoor-activities">
        <h2 class="main__title">Outdoor Activities in Canada</h2>
        <p class="main__text">From the mountains to the lakes, Canada is an outdoor lover's dream. Here are some activities you can enjoy:</p>
        <ul class="activities-list">
            <li><strong>Skiing & Snowboarding</strong>: Head to the slopes in British Columbia, Alberta, or Quebec for some of the best skiing and snowboarding in North America.</li>
            <li><strong>Hiking</strong>: Explore Canada's vast national parks, including Banff, Jasper, and Yoho, for beautiful hiking trails and scenic views.</li>
            <li><strong>Whale Watching</strong>: The east and west coasts of Canada are perfect for whale watching, with opportunities to spot orcas, humpback whales, and more.</li>
            <li><strong>Canoeing & Kayaking</strong>: Paddle through Canada's pristine lakes and rivers, including the famous Algonquin Park and the stunning Bow River in Alberta.</li>
            <li><strong>Ice Skating</strong>: In winter, skate on outdoor rinks like the Rideau Canal in Ottawa, the longest skating rink in the world.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Cultural Experiences -->
    <section class="cultural-experiences">
        <h2 class="main__title">Cultural Experiences in Canada</h2>
        <p class="main__text">Canada is rich in cultural diversity. Explore these experiences to get a deeper understanding of Canadian life:</p>
        <ul class="cultural-list">
            <li><strong>Canadian Museum of History</strong>: Located in Gatineau, this museum offers an insightful look into Canada’s past, from Indigenous history to modern-day Canada.</li>
            <li><strong>Montreal International Jazz Festival</strong>: One of the world's largest jazz festivals, held every summer in Montreal.</li>
            <li><strong>Toronto International Film Festival (TIFF)</strong>: The premier film festival in North America, attracting movie lovers and stars from all over the world.</li>
            <li><strong>Indigenous Cultural Tours</strong>: Learn about Canada's Indigenous cultures by visiting First Nations communities, museums, and cultural centers across the country.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Conclusion -->
    <section class="conclusion">
        <p class="main__text">Canada offers a wealth of experiences for people of all interests. From the bustling cities to the great outdoors, there's no shortage of places to explore, foods to try, and activities to enjoy. Embrace the diversity and adventure that Canada has to offer!</p>
    </section>

</main>

